message: Michael Maltese left Warner Bros in 1958 to Hanna Barbera and his cartoons he wrote in early production were postponed.

Tijuana Toads, The Ant and the Aardvark, The Blue Racer, Hoot Kloot, and The Dogfather were made for television cartoons because theatrical cartoons for DFE came to a end in 1969. beginning in that year cartoons were now debuting on TV.

Tijuana Toads, The Ant and the Aardvark, The Blue Racer, Hoot Kloot, and The Dogfather were made for television cartoons because theatrical cartoons for DFE came to a end in 1969. beginning in that year cartoons were now debuting on TV.

Due to long production time for theatrical cartoons, Person to Bunny was out of date by 1960, as Edward R. Murrow had left Person to Person and was later replaced by Charles Collingwood. Out of date means lapsed (expired) . It was originally cancelled.
